    "cooking_instructions": [
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Preheat the oven to 180\u00b0C/ 160\u00b0C (fan)/ gas 4</p><p>Rinse your<strong> brown rice</strong>, add it to a pot with plenty of <strong>cold water</strong> and bring to the boil over a high heat</p><p>Once boiling, reduce the heat to medium and cook for 20-25 min or until it's tender with a slight bite</p><p>Once cooked, drain, return it to the pot and keep covered until serving</p>",
            "order": 1,
            "image": "/images/instructions/general-tsos-cod-with-brown-rice-and-broccoli/step-1.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Whilst the rice is cooking, cut your <strong>broccoli</strong> into small florets</p><p>Cut piece of <strong>tin foil</strong> (or two!) approx. the size of A3 paper</p><p>Lay the <strong>broccoli florets</strong> in the middle with your <strong>toasted sesame oil</strong>, 1 tbsp<span class=\"text-danger\"> [1 1/2 tbsp] </span><span class=\"text-purple\">[2 tbsp] </span><strong>water</strong> and a pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and add to a baking tray</p><p>Scrunch the edges of the foil around the broccoli to form a sealed parcel[s]</p><p>Put the tray in the oven for 15 min or until tender</p>",
            "order": 2,
            "image": "/images/instructions/general-tsos-cod-with-brown-rice-and-broccoli/step-2.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Whilst the broccoli is cooking, peel and finely chop (or grate) your <strong>garlic</strong></p><p>Peel (scrape the skin off with a teaspoon) and finely chop (or grate) your<strong> ginger</strong></p>",
            "order": 3,
            "image": "/images/instructions/general-tsos-cod-with-brown-rice-and-broccoli/step-3.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Combine 1/2 tsp per person <strong>cornflour</strong> (save the rest for later!), your <strong>soy sauce</strong> and 3 tbsp <span class=\"text-purple\">[4 tbsp] </span><span class=\"text-danger\">[5 tbsp]</span> <strong>cold</strong> <strong>water</strong> in a bowl and stir it all together</p><p>Add your <strong>Chinese rice wine </strong>and <strong>honey</strong> and give everything a good mix up \u2013 this is your<strong> honey sauce</strong></p>",
            "order": 4,
            "image": "/images/instructions/general-tsos-cod-with-brown-rice-and-broccoli/step-4.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Cut your<strong> fish fillet[s]</strong> into bite-sized pieces and add them to a bowl, add the <strong>remaining cornflour</strong> and give everything a good mix up until the fish is fully coated</p><p>Heat a large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick) with a very generous drizzle of <strong>vegetable oil</strong> over a high heat, once hot, add the<strong> coated fish </strong>and cook for 4-5<span class=\"text-danger\"> </span>min on each side or until golden \u2013 this is your <strong>golden fish</strong></p><p>Tip: Cooking for 3 or more? You may need to do this in batches!</p>",
            "order": 5,
            "image": "/images/instructions/general-tsos-cod-with-brown-rice-and-broccoli/step-5.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Once the fish is golden, transfer it to a plate and set aside for later</p><p>Tip: Your fish is cooked when it turns opaque and flakes easily</p><p>Carefully pour away most of the <strong>oil</strong> and return the pan to a medium heat</p><p>Add the <strong>chopped garlic</strong>, <strong>chopped</strong> <strong>ginger</strong> and your<strong> chilli flakes </strong>(can't handle the heat? Go easy!) and cook for 1-2 min or until fragrant</p>",
            "order": 6,
            "image": "/images/instructions/general-tsos-cod-with-brown-rice-and-broccoli/step-6.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Once fragrant, add the <strong>honey</strong> <strong>sauce</strong> and cook for 1-2 min or until thick and sticky</p><p>Once the sauce has thickened, return the <strong>golden fish </strong>to the pan and give everything a good mix up</p><p>Cook for 1-2 min further or until the fish is fully coated \u2013 this is your <strong>General Tso's fish</strong></p>",
            "order": 7,
            "image": "/images/instructions/general-tsos-cod-with-brown-rice-and-broccoli/step-7.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Serve the<strong> General Tso's fish </strong>over the<strong> cooked brown rice </strong>with the <strong>broccoli</strong> to the side</p><p>Garnish with your <strong>toasted sesame seeds</strong></p><p>Enjoy!</p>",
            "order": 8
        }
    ],
